# Tailwind CSS Standards

## Semantic Config — Required

Always use semantic token names in Tailwind config. Never hardcode hex values in classes.

### Required Color Tokens

```
background, surface, surface-alt
primary, primary-hover
accent, accent-hover
text-main, text-muted, text-dim
border, border-hover
glass, glass-hover
```

### Required Font Tokens

```
display → headings
body    → body text
```

## Version Rules

- Tailwind v4 (Astro/Vite): define tokens with `@theme {}` in CSS
- Tailwind v3 (vanilla): define in `tailwind.config.js` > `extend.colors`
- Template available at `templates/tailwind.config.template.js`

## Figma Mapping

Semantic names map directly to Figma design tokens:
- `bg-primary` → Paint Style `Brand / primary`
- `text-text-main` → Paint Style `Text / text-main`
- `font-display` → Text Style `font-display / ...`

See `figma-export` skill for full nomenclature.

## Forbidden

- `bg-[#123456]` — arbitrary hex in classes
- Mixing generic and semantic names
- Uncommmented config variables
